      "content": "yea i get that shrinkage is a thing but it feels like more than just 'misplacing' stuff since it's always these tiny amounts of high-value components. like, exactly 1 or 2 pieces here and there. is there anything else besides just human error or bad counting that might cause these specific kinds of small, recurring gaps?",
